{
  "texts": [
    "These approaches achieve notable performance metrics, with IoU and mIoU ranging from 80 to 86%.",
    "Meanwhile, in the context of instance segmentation, methods like Mask-RCNN and AFD-UNet are employed to precisely delineate individual object instances within an image, contributing to efficient real-time waste collection, accurate medical image interpretation, and more.",
    "The papers highlight the benefits of these techniques, including enhanced boundary delineation, reduced manual intervention, and substantial time savings, while acknowledging challenges such as computational complexity, model customization, and hardware limitations.",
    "This compilation provides a comprehensive understanding of the strengths and challenges of deep learning-based semantic and instance segmentation techniques across diverse application domains.",
    "This review explores deep learning methodologies tailored to different types of image feature extraction across varied application domains."
  ]
}